<sect2 id="sect_definingNormalElements" label="5">
    <title id="title_definingNormalElements">Defining normal elements in a form</title>
    <informaltable frame="none">
        <tgroup rowsep="0" cols="2" align="left" colsep="0">
            <colspec colwidth="1*"/>
            <colspec colwidth="3*"/>
            <tbody>
                <row>
                    <entry/>
                    <entry rowsep="1"/>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Purpose</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>In comparison to <glossterm linkend="DBElement">DB
                            elements</glossterm> normal Elements are GUI elements that are not
                            directly tied to a table field, but encapsulate a certain business logic.</para>
                        <para>They can show e.g. calculated values and are normally controlled by
                                <glossterm linkend="GUIHook">GUI hooks</glossterm>.</para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Normal elements</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para>The following <guibutton>Normal Elements</guibutton> exist: </para>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Text</guimenuitem> and <guimenuitem>Long
                                    text</guimenuitem> fields: </para>
                                <para>can display e.g. the calculated total price of an order.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Checkboxes</guimenuitem>:</para>
                                <para>can show e.g. a calculated state.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Comboboxes</guimenuitem>:</para>
                                <para>can e.g. restrict the selection of enum values due to the
                                    values of other fields in the form.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Time</guimenuitem>, <guimenuitem>Date</guimenuitem>
                                    and <guimenuitem>Timestamp</guimenuitem> fields:</para>
                                <para>can e.g. display calculated delivery dates.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Labels</guimenuitem>:</para>
                                <para>give you the possibility to define captions somewhere in a
                                    group, e.g. an &#8364; sign behind a text field containing a price.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <guimenuitem>Own Draw</guimenuitem> elements:</para>
                                <para>make it possible to draw your own images, symbols in a group,
                                    e.g. a progress bar.</para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry>
                        <para>
                            <emphasis>Procedure</emphasis>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                    <entry rowsep="1">
                        <para> Proceed the following steps to define a <glossterm
                                linkend=" normalElement">normal element</glossterm> in a group:</para>
                        <para>
                            <informaltable rowsep="1" colsep="1" frame="all">
                                <tgroup cols="2">
                                    <colspec align="center" colwidth="1*"/>
                                    <colspec align="left" colwidth="6*"/>
                                    <thead>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>Step</entry>
                                            <entry align="center">Procedure</entry>
                                        </row>
                                    </thead>
                                    <tbody>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>1</para>
                                            </entry>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>Load the form containing the group to be
                                                  edited into the form editor.</para>
                                            </entry>
                                        </row>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>2</para>
                                            </entry>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>Select the desired normal element from the
                                                  <guibutton>Normal Elements</guibutton> menu
                                                  in the form editor.</para>
                                            </entry>
                                        </row>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>3</para>
                                            </entry>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>Place the normal element at the desired
                                                  position in the group edited by pressing the
                                                  left mouse button.</para>
                                            </entry>
                                        </row>
                                        <row>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>4</para>
                                            </entry>
                                            <entry>
                                                <para>Add the appropriate business logic to the
                                                  normal element by creating and editing the event
                                                  handler of the GUI element as described in the
                                                  section ....ADD link to section!!!</para>
                                            </entry>
                                        </row>
                                    </tbody>
                                </tgroup>
                            </informaltable>
                        </para>
                    </entry>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <entry/>
                    <entry/>
                </row>
            </tbody>
        </tgroup>
    </informaltable>
</sect2>
